# Complete Backend API Specification — PEREMPUAN AMAN

## Overview

This document maps **every feature** in the frontend to the REST API endpoints needed to make the site fully dynamic with admin login and content management.

**Convention**: All endpoints return JSON. Protected endpoints require `Authorization: Bearer <token>`.

```
🔓 = Public (no auth)
🔒 = Admin only (requires auth)
```

---

## 1. Authentication & User Management

No auth exists in the frontend yet — these endpoints power a new admin login system.

| Method | Endpoint | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/auth/register` | 🔒 | Create new admin (super-admin only) |
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | 🔓 | Login, returns JWT access + refresh tokens |
| POST | `/api/auth/refresh` | 🔓 | Refresh expired access token |
| GET | `/api/auth/me` | 🔒 | Get current user profile |
| PUT | `/api/auth/me` | 🔒 | Update profile / password |
| POST | `/api/auth/logout` | 🔒 | Invalidate refresh token |

**Login request/response**:
```json
// POST /api/auth/login
{ "email": "admin@perempuanaman.or.id", "password": "..." }

// Response
{
  "accessToken": "eyJ...",
  "refreshToken": "...",
  "user": { "id": 1, "name": "Admin", "email": "...", "role": "admin" }
}
```

---

## 2. File / Media Upload

Many resources reference images and PDFs. This is the centralized upload endpoint.

| Method | Endpoint | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/upload` | 🔒 | Upload image or PDF, returns URL |
| DELETE | `/api/upload/:filename` | 🔒 | Delete an uploaded file |

**Response**:
```json
{ "url": "/uploads/images/1708123456-photo.jpg", "filename": "1708123456-photo.jpg" }
```

> [!TIP]
> For production, use cloud storage (S3, Google Cloud Storage, or Cloudinary) instead of local filesystem.

---

## 3. Berita / Catatan Perempuan Adat (Articles)

**Source files**: [beritaData.js](file:///home/user/Documents/Github/frontend-perempuanaman/data/beritaData.js) — WordPress-like structure with HTML content

**Frontend pages**: homepage [Berita](file:///home/user/Documents/Github/frontend-perempuanaman/components/Berita/Berita.js#4-130) section, `/publikasi/catatan`, `/publikasi/catatan/[slug]`

| Method | Endpoint | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/berita` | 🔓 | List articles (paginated, searchable) |
| GET | `/api/berita/:slug` | 🔓 | Single article by slug |
| POST | `/api/berita` | 🔒 | Create new article |
| PUT | `/api/berita/:id` | 🔒 | Update article |
| DELETE | `/api/berita/:id` | 🔒 | Delete article |
| GET | `/api/berita/categories` | 🔓 | List unique category names |

**Query params**: `?search=`, `?category=`, `?tag=`, `?page=1`, `?per_page=9`, `?sort=date`

**Data shape**:
```json
{
  "id": 1001,
  "slug": "perempuan-adat-nusantara-membangun-kedaulatan-pangan",
  "title": "Perempuan Adat Nusantara Membangun...",
  "date": "2024-05-12T10:00:00",
  "categoryName": "Kedaulatan Pangan",
  "tags": ["Ketahanan Pangan", "Krisis Iklim"],
  "excerpt": "<p>Short summary HTML...</p>",
  "content": "<p>Full article HTML...</p>",
  "featuredImage": "/uploads/images/article-cover.jpg"
}
```

**Paginated list response**:
```json
{
  "data": [ /* array of articles */ ],
  "meta": { "currentPage": 1, "totalPages": 5, "totalItems": 42, "perPage": 9 }
}
```

> [!NOTE]
> The current frontend uses a WordPress-like nested shape (`title.rendered`, `_embedded.wp:featuredmedia`). When building the backend, use the flat shape above and update the frontend to match — it's much simpler.

