## Implementation Priority

### Phase 1 — Foundation (Build First)
1. **Auth** — Login/JWT system
2. **Upload** — File handling
3. **Berita** — Largest, most complex content type
4. **Wilayah** — Powers the interactive map

### Phase 2 — Core Content
5. **Pengurus** + **Sekretariat** — People profiles
6. **Audit** + **Pustaka** — PDF document management
7. **Capaian** — Strategic data tables

### Phase 3 — Media & Extras
8. **Gallery** — Photo management
9. **Tutur** — Podcast episodes
10. **Alur** — Formation process
11. **Programs** — Kerja Kami content

### Phase 4 — Polish
12. **Settings/Pages** — CMS for static pages
13. **Stats** — Homepage counters
14. **Donasi** — Donation tracking

---

## Tech Stack Recommendation

| Layer | Recommended |
|---|---|
| **Runtime** | Node.js (matches your Next.js frontend) |
| **Framework** | Express.js or Fastify |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL (relational data fits well) or MongoDB |
| **ORM** | Prisma (PostgreSQL) or Mongoose (MongoDB) |
| **Auth** | JWT (access + refresh tokens) with bcrypt |
| **File Storage** | Local `/uploads` for dev → S3/Cloudinary for prod |
| **Validation** | Joi or Zod |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Since your frontend is Next.js, you could also use **Next.js API Routes** (`app/api/...`) to co-locate your backend with the frontend — eliminating CORS issues and simplifying deployment.
